general.description:
I help CommBank market itself as a great place to work. I spend my days looking for innovative ways to attract the people we need for our business by telling the authentic story of what it is really like to work here. Whether it’s through Employee Advocacy, our Virtual Reality Experience, Video Role Profiles, Careers Page or Social Media, we bring the story of working at CommBank to life. 

At the moment I'm focused on driving Employee Advocacy across CommBank and encouraging our employees to tell their own authentic stories of #CommBankLife.

I have recruited into the financial services industry for over 5 years, gaining experience in agency, outsourced and in-house recruitment as well as sales and delivery leadership. I've always been passionate about helping people build their careers because I know that finding the right job can be key to a person’s happiness and wellbeing. I’ve also seen time and time again how the right employee can be the key to a business’ success.

When I’m not at work, I’m usually in the middle of some kind of 30 day Yoga Challenge or am trying to teach my rebellious puppy to follow any basic commands. It's a work in progress!

Since we were founded in the Queensland outback in 1920 as Queensland and Northern Territory Aerial Services Limited, Qantas has grown to be Australia's largest domestic and international airline.

general.headline: Operating Partner at Liverpool Partners
general.description:
I have had over 25 years experience in the health care sector throughout Australia, Asia and Europe. During this time I have held both senior financial and management roles at a business unit level together with group executive roles with responsibility over multiple business units.

I have had direct experience in the management of private hospitals, medical centers, pathology, radiology, nutraceutical manufacturing and pharmacy distribution businesses.

During my career I have held executive director roles in private and publicly listed healthcare companies with turnover of up to in excess of $3 billion.

jobs.description:
Craigcare provides aged care facilities and services in Western Australia and Victoria.
      
      The network currently consists of  750 beds across the two states.

Life Healthcare Ltd listed on the Australian stock exchange late 2013 after 5 years of
      private equity ownership. The company is a specialized distributor of medical devices
      
      to the hospital sector throughout Australia.
Private equity owned private hospital group.

Managing Director specializing in consulting in the healthcare industry throughout
      Australia, Asia and Europe - primarily focusing on operational reviews and assisting
      
      private equity firms conduct due diligence on potential acquisition targets.

Healthscope Limited owns and operates 44 private hospitals, pathology services and 59 medical centres throughout Australia with turnover in excess of A$2billion.

Healthscope was a publicly listed company that was privatised in 2010 by a private equity consortium. I was approached to replace the incumbent CFO prior to the takeover and assisted the consortium during due diligence.

Upon commencement in the role it became clear to the new executive that a significant management, structural and cultural change would be required. Key strategies to achieve this were to make significant changes to management at both a corporate and hospital level, a re-organisation of corporate structure and service model, cost reduction initiatives through hospital benchmarking exercise and the implementation of a comprehensive management reporting and KPI framework.  We also identified significant brownfields opportunity ($500 million+) and set about completing detailed feasibilities and commencement of many projects.

Healthbridge Pty Limited is private equity backed start up business investing in IVF and pathology. 
In the space of two years the business acquired various IVF and pathology businesses with turnover in excess of $120m.

As the Finance Director I was involved in conducting the due diligence, valuations and negotiations with doctors. Once we acquired sufficient scale, the focus changed to integration of the businesses and improving financial performance. This required setting a new strategic direction for the group, implementation of new financial systems, reports and key performance indicators.

A colleague and myself established a consulting company focusing on operational improvement in the healthcare sector. This involved conducting hospital and corporate efficiency reviews utilizing our unique benchmarking tools developed over the last decade during our time in senior management roles at large healthcare organisations.  We also assisted private equity firms, public and private companies conduct due diligence and valuations of various businesses throughout Australia, Asia (Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand, Philippines, India) and Europe (UK, Turkey and Spain).

In late 2008 we were approached by a private equity firm to join Healthbridge Pty Ltd.

jobs.jobTitle: Chief Financial Officer/Executive Director of Strategy & Business Development
jobs.description:
Symbion Health Limited operated pathology and radiology services together with medical centres, pharmaceutical wholesaling and nutraceutical manufacturing and distribution. Annual turnover $3.8 billion.

Symbion was seen as an underperforming business relative to it's peers. I was approached by the then Board to become the Chief Financial Officer. Together with a newly appointed CEO our goal was to improve the underlying financial performance of the business to at least that of its peers.  During this period the management team focused on new initiatives, including a significant change in management personnel, the introduction of improved financial reporting and key performance indicators and the rationalisation of underperforming businesses.

Affinity Health Limited was the largest owner and operator of private hospitals in Australia with 50 hospitals in Australia and 3 in Indonesia. Annual turnover  $1.4 billion.

Affinity Health was acquired from Mayne Group in 2003 for approximately $800 million by a consortium of private equity groups. The business was in distress after some well documented failed strategies implemented by Mayne Group.

The new executive focused on implementing significant cultural change and strategies to re-engage with doctors and staff to re-build confidence in the business. We also implemented a comprehensive set of key performance indicators covering all aspects of the business (qualitative and quantitative). We then set about establishing peer groups (small groups of like for like (casemix/service provision) hospitals and  introduced benchmarking (qualitative and quantitative) across these peer groups to drive best practice. As a result of these strategies the business rapidly improved its financial and qualitative performance. In 2005 it was decided by shareholders and management to offer the business for sale. A dual track (trade sale or ASX listing) process was established. During this process I led the due diligence process for the potential trade sale and preparation of a fully complete prospectus for the potential listing.

During this period I held various hospital finance roles, moving to Chief Executive Officer of individual private hospitals located in Victoria and Western Australia. I was also General Manager of medical centers in Western Australia, during which time I oversaw the acquisition, amalgamation and construction of in excess of 20 medical centres.

In 2002 I was appointed General Manager Finance for the entire network of 53 private hospitals across Australia and Indonesia.

During this period I gained a detailed understanding of the operations and management of private hospitals. I was a key driver in the development of detailed key performance indicators and benchmarking tools that wereadopted across the entire group.  I also played a key role in the due diligence and early negotiations with the Western Australian Health Department for the establishment of the privatised Joondalup Health Campus.

In early 2003 Mayne Group decided to sell the hospital division, as General Manager Finance for the division I led the due diligence process on the sell side. The business was ultimately sold to a private equity and management consortium and Affinity Health Limited was formed. I was offered the role of Chief Financial Officer of Affinity.

general.headline: Integrated Business Planning | Business Project Management
general.description:
I am a driven and versatile business project leader and management professional; with more than 15 years industry experience across the resource, manufacturing, defence, energy, consulting and strategic marketing services sectors in some of Australia’s largest enterprises such as Sensis and Origin Energy.  My capabilities in Planning, Business Project Management & Change Management have been acquired during my broad experience in bringing people together at a senior leadership level to develop strategic visions and plans for the organisation and working collaboratively with others to bring strategy to life; from market planning and new product feasibility assessment through to business case development and ultimately implementation. 
I have a natural ability to build trusted relationships with stakeholders at all levels and I thrive in situations that have a challenge and the complexity of the unknown about them.  
My experience is supported by my practitioner status in Prince 2 and Agile project management as well as Change Setter accreditation.

jobs.description:
Key Roles and Responsibilities
Develop and lead the implementation of the Integrated Business Planning process in ANZ across all 7 strategic business units and common supportive functions.  In doing so, the business strategy is consistently deployed and used to direct the business decision making process.
Implement Product Reviews to clarify and review the product strategy, driving product portfolio and life-cycle planning.  Implement Demand Reviews in order to create unconstrained Demand Plans detailing the market demands for the next 24 months.  Implement Supply Reviews, incorporating the functions of purchasing and logistics as well as supply chain and operations, in order to create a 24 month supply plan based on the SBU demand plans.
Track assumptions, vulnerabilities and opportunities in order to do scenario planning and foresee the future.
Set up business unit reconciliation meeting and a Management Business Review to review and finalise business plans, as well as make any decisions that have to be made at the leadership level.

Key Achievements
Recipient of the PPG Global Supply Chain Titan award 
Constructed the Supply Review Strategy and Vision through a facilitated process
Oliver Wight certifications in Demand Management, Integrated Tactical Planning and Integrated Business Planning
Saved $200k of working capital on one product launch through scenario identification & implementation
Established a portfolio tracking tool and enhanced product funnel
Established the full working business planning cycle in the 2 largest business units.  Successfully negotiated the enhanced alignment of the 5 smaller business units to the business planning cycle.

Nutrition Technologies is a biotechnology start-up located just out of Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam, developing a range of products derived from the Black Soldier Fly larvae. The larvae are fed on organic waste streams and processed into usable products such as oils, protein powders and fertiliser. The primary focus of this global internship was on product and process development.

This internship gave me the opportunity to gain work and cultural experiences in a dynamic country, as well as a being able to live, work and study in Vietnam. 

Independent research was conducted on the oil extracted from the solar dried Black Soldier Fly larvae. A two stage project was to analyse the chemical make up of the oil and its potential uses in Industrial applications, pharmaceuticals and animal feedstocks. Research and experimental data was also used to identify chemical additives for storage and stabilisation. Intellectual Property reports were created to cover filtration techniques, neutralisation and stabilisation of the sustainable oil. 
The Internship with Nutrition Technologies offered the opportunity to engage with all areas of the business including operations, marketing, research and development and business administration.

general.description:
David is a director of Lean Sigma Analytics and a founding partner of Lean Sigma Institute.  Lean Sigma Analytics applies predictive analytics, and Big Data methods to create dashboards that link organisational strategy to improvement initiatives leading to business excellence. It does this in partnership with, Information Builders, a large US software company. 
Lean Sigma Institute develops drivers of improvement in organisations that have the knowledge, skills and competence to make improvement happen. 
David has over 20 years experience in organisational development and business improvement, half of that in Sweden before moving to Australia. He has extensive experience in education, training and consulting to facilitate business improvement with a track record of successful improvement projects, in a wide range of industries and company sizes.

jobs.description:
AREAS OF EXPERTISE 
 Acquisition consulting | Staff training  | Equipment sales and support | Inventory Management | Risk Management | Project Management Change Management | Financial Management | Business Strategy | Leadership Development Cross-Functional Team Leadership | Mentoring Organizational Effectiveness | Logistics/Workshop Management – multi site management Managing Employees | Staff Development | Team Building Policies | Human Resources | Recruiting 
Customer Relations 

CORE COMPETENCIES 
• Excellent people manager – Persuader, influencer, leader, negotiator and delegator. 
• Team work – Effectively communicates to delegate responsibilities using interpersonal skills. 
• Accuracy and punctuality – Precise with details and facts. 
• Assisted accident repair companies in Australia with overseas staffing as well as my within own businesses. 
• Good understanding of lean production methods, ISO standards, bench marking, hourly rates, budgets, etc. I can also read and understand financial reports. 
KEY FUNCTIONS 
• Played a significant role in long-term strategic plans toward operational excellence – Developed long-range forecasts and maintained long-range financial plans, developed and implemented organizational strategies and policies. 
• Supervised and increased effectiveness and efficiency of operational systems and processes/policies to support organisation’s mission; specifically, supported management reporting/information. 
• Focal point for creating annual budget and monitoring cash flow – Developed and managed annual budgets and program budgets. 
• Supervised overall financial system, HR management, IT system and business controls. 
• Supervised and coached office and workshop managers on a daily basis. 
• Reviewed monthly activity reports, fulfilled tax related requirements and generated year-end reports. 
• Administered employee payroll, benefits and insurance.

Helping accident repair business with profitability, management and efficiency's through smart  equipment purchases and our cloud based management software package. We help businesses to manage employment records, equipment maintenance and purchasing, calendars, tasks, BMS, OH&S, staff recruitment, cloud based document storage, contacts and other items.

Having sold my successful Car Craft accident repair  businesses, I decided to take a break from the industry and pursue other hobbies and interests.  I set up a part time mountain bike tour company taking small groups of experience riders into Northern Thailand and to race events in SEA. This business was more of a hobby for me and in 2016 I handed it over to a long term Thai friend

In 2009 I opened Cockburn Car Craft one of Perth’s premier repair facilities. In 2010 Cockburn Car Craft won the AAMI Bodyshop of the year award. This was a great accomplishment as two of the finalists were an Audi repair shop in Sydney and a Mercedes repair business in Melbourne.
In 2011 this business came second in the Car Craft Group for ‘best repairer’ based on profit, efficiencies  and systems. I employed sixteen tradesmen within the business.

In my time as a director of the Car Craft group I had many tasks from customer complaints, marketing, staff requirement, workshop mentoring, arranging functions, supplier contracts strategic planning plus much more. I found this position challenging at times as I had different views but also rewarding helping others grow.

In 2001 I started Port Kennedy Car Craft as a new business. I implemented my ISO 9001 and 1400 system that I worked with in my past business since day one. After a few years operating from  rented premises I built a purpose built factory and once we relocated and expanded saw a huge growth within the business. When I sold this business to the Gemini Group in January 2014 we had twelve trade staff doing day shift and night shift. At the time no other accident repair business in Perth was doing shift work to optimise work bays.  We had fixed cost arrangements with insurance companies and where the second repairer in Perth to do this type of arrangement.

In 2005 I started Port Kennedy Repco Auto Service as a new business. This auto service workshop was a purpose build workshop that I built along with the Port Kennedy Accident repair business. The two businesses worked well next to each other however within a few years both businesses ran out of room due to rapid expansion. It was then I purchased some land and build the new automotive service workshop and relocated the business.
In 2009 I sold the business to the store manager who currently operates the business today.

Estimator
I worked at Combined Smash Repairs as a part time estimator 3 days a week.  The owner at the time, Ken Wilson, wanted me to work full time but this was not suitable for me at the time due to other commitments.

In 1997 an opportunity came up to purchase what was Johnson’s Car Craft at the time. The business was making significant losses monthly and the owners had other business interests so wanted out. After hard work and implementing best business practices I changed the business around to be profitable with less staff.

This success saw the first accident repair business in Australia to be 3rd party certified in not only ISO 9001 but ISO 1400 the environmental system.

I started my role at Melville car craft as a panel beater, within the first few months I was promoted to a supervisor’s role. Within my first year of employment I took the position of Manager with approximately 30 staff.

Once I completed by apprenticeship I started my first business with just myself and employed one spray painter.  This business focussed on mainly repairing cars for car dealerships as well as insurance claims.

I commenced my apprenticeship with this company and believed I was fortunate that I spent my apprenticeship learning how to repair accident damaged prestige vehicles, which were mainly Mercedes. I repaired everything from small jobs through to major smash work on Celette and Car bench repair systems.  After my four years apprenticeship I acquired my Panel Beating Trade Certificate.

general.headline: Chief Technology Officer at Qantas
general.description:
Involved in IT and Technology innovation for over 15 years, with experience in software engineering and management, I have been involved with many start-ups and consulting engagements.

In 2005, I helped establish Aegeon. Aegeon evolved to providing consulting capabilities around IT Strategy and Architecture, Web Innovation, Agile delivery and Product Development for many leading companies in Australia and around the world. It quickly grew to over $2 Million in Revenue and 30 employees in the first year.

My role also included implementing and growing of an Agile delivery team, sourcing and securing an Offshore Development Centre in China as well as being the technical face of the company, speaking at many conferences and engagements on Aegeon, and Web Innovation.

I was the CTO of Posse.com, where I was responsible for delivering the technology platform that runs the business. This includes everything from architecting the solution, managing the team and writing the code for the product.

Most recently, I was the Chief Technology Officer of Echo Entertainment; a casino organisation that owns and operates 4 casinos on the east coast of Australia, The Star in Sydney, Jupiters Gold Coast & Townsville and Treasury in Brisbane. My role included driving technology strategy and innovation across the group.

Currently, I am the Director of IT at William Hill Australia. A sports & race wagering & gaming organisation from the UK, William Hill recently expanded its operations into Australia by purchasing SportingBet, CentreBet and Tom Waterhouse. The role includes challenges in growing an IT organisation to sustain the business's massive uplift in growth in this region.

Specialties: I have an engineering background with over 15 years of experience in technology. This has also stemmed into Architecture & Strategy, Business Process Engineering and Analysis as well as Project and Program management. I also have a passion evangelizing innovation and the Social Web.

general.headline: CEO - Fox Special Projects at Linfox
general.description:
Ari Suss is Chief Executive Officer of Fox Special Projects Group, supporting the family investment arm of the Linfox Group of Companies and a Board Member of Avalon Airport Australia. 

Ari joined Linfox in 2004 as Manager of Government and Corporate Affairs providing specialist expertise in regulatory, legislative and political matters for the company’s logistics, property and aviation businesses. In 2008 Ari became Executive Director of Fox Private Group. Between 1999 and 2004, Ari was a senior adviser to former Premier Steve Bracks. During this time he specialised in policy and advice in the areas of infrastructure development, transport, ports, major projects, multicultural affairs and parliamentary strategy.

In 2011, Ari also commenced in his role as General Manager of the Australian Automotive Research Centre, a 1000 hectare vehicle test facility in Anglesea, Victoria. 

In October 2015, Ari was appointed a Director and Board Member of Goulburn Murray Water.

Ari has a Master's degree in Public Policy and Management from Monash University and has completed executive studies at Harvard Business School.

jobs.description:
Fed Square is managed by Fed Square Pty Ltd, which was established by the Victorian
      Government in 1999. Fed Square Pty Ltd is responsible for the co-ordination and
      management of self-governing tenancies, programming and marketing of all the public
      
      spaces and all aspects of asset management and development.

Goulburn-Murray Rural Water Corporation trading as Goulburn-Murray Water (GMW) is a statutory Corporation constituted by Ministerial order under the provisions of the Water Act 1989.

GMW has functions and powers to store, manage and deliver water across most of Northern Victoria, including manage and operate an irrigation district (section 221), a water district (section 163) and a waterway management district (section 189).

GMW services a region of 68,000 square kilometres, bordered by the Great Dividing Range to the south, the River Murray to the north and stretching from Corryong in the east to Nyah in the west.

The Australian Automotive Research Centre (AARC) offers an extensive range of automotive engineering services to all vehicle and component manufacturers.

AARC occupies a 1000 hectare site near Anglesea, 125km south-west of Melbourne and is the largest privately owned independently operated automotive testing facility in Australia.

Avalon Airport is the only low-cost commercial airport in Victoria. While the airport keeps costs to a minimum, it aims to provide passengers and visitors with the facilities expected at airports around Australia.

Avalon started commercial operation with Jetstar in 2004. Since then, the number of Jetstar flights has risen substantially and in November 2010 Tiger Airways started flying into and out of the facility. As a result, the airport has expanded to accommodate the increasing demand and passenger throughput.

The Carlton Football Club (nicknamed The Blues) is an Australian rules football club in the Australian Football League (AFL). 

The Blues are the third oldest club in the Australian Football League and one of the oldest Australian rules football clubs. 

The club were the first premiers of the Victorian Football Association (VFA) in 1877 and, along with Essendon, share the most premierships of any VFL/AFL club with 16.

The club originally represented the inner city Melbourne area of Carlton and its nickname comes from the navy blue colour of its uniform

general.headline: Retail Executive & Thought Leader | Founder, CLX | Maximising Return Through Customer Experience (CX) Transformation
general.description:
I empower retailers to deliver customer-led front-end change, in a way that maximises shareholder return.  
Leveraging two decades of success in retail transformation, I know how to navigate through the challenges and opportunities presented by change. Delivering at scale is complex, yet I have proven that by building focused teams and equipping them with tenacity, capacity and trust, transformation can not only deliver efficiencies, it can revolutionise company value propositions. For me, it’s about driving the buzz of benefits realisation. 
The experience I bring to CLX Professionals spans the UK and Australia, where I have worked with retail giants such as Sainsbury’s, Coles and Travelex to transform front-end business operations into customer focused and highly optimised environments. I’ve led multimillion-dollar transformation projects encompassing checkouts, software deployments and cultural transformation, all of which have placed customer experience at the core of the solution. I have enabled and realised measurable commercial returns, including YOY growth, improved customer satisfaction and multimillion-dollar cost savings – all with the goal of driving reinvestment back into the business, its team members and of course, its customers. 
In 2017, I founded specialist consultancy CLX Professionals to empower more retailers to embrace the pace of change in the industry, maximising shareholder return by creating unique customer experiences. Aligning emerging technology and best practice with unique retail environments, we build competitive differentiation, assessing and prioritising solutions based on ROI, and enabling organisations and their C-suite/executive teams to deliver sustainable results quickly via accelerated roll out and tight benefits tracking. 

If you would like to find out more about CLX and how it can support your retail business, please free free to get in touch via LinkedIn.

general.headline: Project Manager at Energy Australia
general.description:
With over 14 years’ experience in projects/programs, Samantha has strong disciplines and standards gained through working across numerous industries & sectors.  A team player who loves to get her hands dirty to deliver tangible business outcomes, and is equally confident leading small-medium IT & business projects with specialised people in cross-functional teams to ensure the project’s realization.

Over time, Sam has learned, developed and cultured her skills and ethics from managers and colleagues - always taking the best attributes with her.  With solid expertise in stakeholder management, program governance and quality assurance reporting, deliverable / milestone tracking, risk / issue management, processes, document management and complex vendor administration, she is committed to accuracy and results, always highly-motivated to work independently and as part of a strong and capable team.  

Sam is a natural leader with continuous energy and enthusiasm when liaising and communicating with diverse ranges of key stakeholders at all levels, to positively influence, guide and team-build during times of organisational change.  Her interpersonal and communication skills (both verbal and written) are displayed with a comprehensive attention to detail, and duty of care for effective team / stakeholder / client / vendor relationships. 

Her track record as a strong and dynamic Project/Program Coordinator built the foundation to take on the full responsibilities and accountabilities of Project Management. And it is the same qualities and capabilities that consistently allow her to focus and achieve both the individual tasks-at-hand and the overall delivery of projects and programs. 

Sam is very capable to own, coordinate & manage the delivery of work, whilst taking guidance from her colleagues & stakeholders who all share in a common goal of successful outcomes.  Having worked in a number of industries, her determination and style makes her a valuable asset.

jobs.description:
Connect is an EA customer wide program (Connect CP, Connect CE and Connect Quality) investing in the capability development of our leaders and front-line staff.  It is a significant transformation of the customer culture at EA touching over 2000 employees across our teams both onshore and offshore.  The Connect Program incorporates capability development for the delivery of consistent high quality customer conversations (front line) & a consistent operating rhythm incorporating technology to provide governance & transparency of effectiveness. 

Connect is split into 3 primary areas:
•	Conversation behaviour & quality uplift through training, coaching
•	Leadership accountability & commitment to Connect operating rhythm
•	Support through Technology and Process

Sam took on a Snr PC role to support the Connect PM/SME to administer & regulate the project with planning, financials & procurement, steering committee reporting, EPMO governance framework & controls, communications, document management, stakeholder management, vendor management & execution plus the complex logistical coordination to implement all training activities throughout the CP Sales Centres. 

Additional tasks include:
•	Planning, management & delivery of the high profile Connect Program launch working alongside an external vendor creative production team to ensure all event logistics were in place
•	Coordinating & integrating all customer facing consultant & leader training & coaching activities across multiple functional lines, working alongside the vendor & facilitators
•	Supporting business case development including PMP & financial model, whilst coordinating all Investment Committee submission documentation together with required sign-offs and functional reviews
•	Managing complex procurement requirements of vendor sourcing, RFQ, SOW/contract signoffs & SAP generation to invoice payment of suppliers / 3rd parties, whilst working with the program accountant ensure accurate forecasting & accruals

jobs.jobTitle: Senior Project Analyst / Project Manager - Customer Transformation Program
jobs.description:
The Customer Experience (CX) workstream was established as part of CTP with the objective to provide a Customer Led approach using Human Centred Design (HCD), for the transformation program.  Utilising agile ways of working, CX articulated what the great customer experiences of the future could be, providing the output in a format that the program and business could action by aligning to key enablers of People, Process, Technology and Data.  By using a transitional approach, CX provided recommendations of future implementations within the ongoing Operating Model for EA (in terms of framework tools and roles).

With the CX workstream moving into its transitional phase, Sam has taken on the role to support the full CTP Operating Model (OM) team, comprising of 5 leads.  Using SAFe principles, the scope is to further detail how the future capabilities would be integrated into EA operations.  Through various projects, exploration is being undertaken of how the core skills of Customer at the Core, Digital in the DNA & Business Agility would be operationalised.

Tasks include:
• Supporting the Operating Model, Customer Experience, Incubator, Design for Scale & Digital Delivery Project Manager / Workstream Leads, as well as their associated 35 team members, to achieve the projects objectives of defined scope, timeline, budget and quality specified
• Administering and regulating the projects, including reporting, budget, schedule, resources, quality, risks & issues
• Coordinating and integrating activities across multiple functional lines, and contributing to stakeholder communications 
• Assisting the management of functional teams and individual resources including a number of vendors to deliver the project products
• Managing the complex procurement requirements of vendor sourcing, RFQ, SOW/contract signoffs and SAP generation through to invoice payment of suppliers / 3rd parties, whilst working closely with the program accountant to ensure accurate forecasting & accruals

As one of the few experienced Project Managers within the ServiceNow Platform space at Telstra, Sam was again assigned to deliver numerous high profile programs of work for GES stakeholders.  Similar to the previous program, this role involved creating multiple custom applications on the ServiceNow platform transforming various existing business applications onto one cloud based platform. 

Capturing all GES Sales based opportunities, the Opportunity Tracking Application (SWOT) and the Requirements Mapping Application (SNAPPER) enabled workflow automation, approval processes, notifications and the capability to produce accurate and customisable reporting on all opportunities each team or individual is engaged in. 

Sam was then asked to move into a Transformation Specialist position to work directly with the GES team (internal client) to support the delivery of the above programs of work.  With her knowledge & experience in managing the implementation of the ServiceNow platform, she was able to guide & assist the internal team to capture & source specific functional requirements from various Telstra groups, streamlining the information directly to the developers.  

This enabled a faster & more accurate documentation & development of the ServiceNow applications, hence reducing the implementation & delivery timelines for the client.  

Tasks included:
•	Planning and management of pre implementation, implementation and support activities
•	Complex Stakeholder Management - coordination point for internal teams, vendors and project resources
•	Creation of project schedules inc milestones and tracking / monitoring deliverables
•	Managing project requirements gathering workshops, documentation, data migration, user roles, development, UAT, reporting;
•	SCRUM management of all stories & releases - functional requirements converted into stories to track & manage end to end via Sprints/Releases
•	Management of Transformation Team - Program Lead, Technical Leads, Developers

BESD Transition & Transformation Program

Throughout an ongoing change journey within Telstra, Operations & ITS, Enterprise Services are focusing on simplification, efficiency, better stakeholder management and improved alignment. 

Sam was assigned this challenging high profile project to deliver a workflow management tool, requiring her to perform a very business focused project manager delivery role ensuring rapid design, development and implementation via a phased Agile approach with a vendor software solution. 

Developed on the ServiceNow Platform, the Work Order Management Module (CRISP) implementation enables automation and the capability to produce accurate and customisable reporting on all work each team is engaged in. Now with a centralised front door into Enterprise Services, this single source of truth provides an understanding of demand whilst helping drive process improvement.

The CRISP Program has been consecutively and successfully delivered on schedule over four phases managed within the SCRUM Module. Each phase encompassed Planning, Requirements Gathering, Development, DEV/UAT Testing & Reworks, Deployment, Training/Education and Communications.

Tasks included:
* SCRUM management of all stories & releases - functional requirements gathered, analysed & converted into various stories to track & manage end to end via Sprints/Releases
* Development of a high level workflow, request/sub request/solutions types, assignment rules, Stage/State/Reasons, SLA’s, Metrics providing the ability to on board multiple teams within efficient timeframes
* Improvement, development & rollout of the new Customer Self Service Request Portal 
* Complex Stakeholder Management to on board additional teams & departments
* Documentation of all related requiremens, design, technical and process 
* Phase/Release Communications to all users and stakeholders
* Management of the CRISP Transformation Team - Program Lead, Technical Lead, Business Analyst, 2 x Developers;

My role as AeroShell and International Marine Lubricants Sales Manager is a specialist role intended to grow the AeroShell portfolio in the Australian Market and manage the international marine lubricants trade for Viva Energy Australia.

The AeroShell component of the role meant I was solely responsible for the aviation portfolio in the Australian market for Viva Energy Australia.  The sales aspect of this role was through both direct and indirect channels (through distributors) and invovled managing customer expectations around an evolving reimaged portfolio.  

The International Marine component of my role was effectively working on lubricant sales to international shipping companies throughout Australian ports, liaising with supply chain focal points and being mindful of HSSE requirements.  This role involved working with international shipping companies and involved both spot buys and contracting both traders and shipping lines.

During my time in these roles, I grew customer bases in both roles and saw an increase of sales to Viva Energy Australia.

Following the successful sale of Shell's Downstream Assets to Vitol, I have migrated
      across to Viva Energy Australia as the Industrial Lubricants Business Development
      
      Manager.

Create and generate sales and marketing strategies in line with core business objectives and target segments.  My primary role is to provide subject matter expertise within the upstream and downstream coal seam gas (CSG) and Liquefied Natural Gas (LNG) businesses including construction and OEMs plus working with each of the proponents within the industry. 

Other market segments which I am directly involved with is heavy manufacturing, power generation, and working with the Queensland sales and technical team to ensure adherence to key goals and sales planning to ensure targeted segments of the Queensland industrial lubricants markets are being approached in a coordinated fashion.

As a geographically based Key Account Manager, I was managing a variety of accounts
      from various industries including mining, sugar production, power generation, defense
      
      contractors, franchised workshops and distributor customers.

MacAir Airlines was a leading regional airline servicing the fly-in/fly-out minerals sectors and communities of Northern and South Western Queensland.

Created, implemented and reviewed marketing initiatives including advertising, experiential marketing, community sponsorship and liaison.  In addition, I was responsible for stakeholder engagement including managing Queensland Department of Transport contract obligations and working with community groups and council within the regional areas of Queensland that were serviced by the airline.

My primary role with North Queensland Newspapers in Townsville was as an advertising sales consultant for three insert publications - the Rural Bulletin, Industry North and Prime Time.  My position was autonomous in which I was responsible for achieving sales targets and managing the day to day administration and some editorial functions of the publications.

general.description:
I'm a strategically minded leader focused on providing vision & direction that positions organisations to embrace change. 

Working with leading and challenger companies, I’ve made an impact by cutting to the core of complex issues, identifying solutions, and communicating them in a compelling and accessible way. I’m a confident relationship builder at all organisational levels and have had the pleasure of developing high calibre teams.

My ethos is: 
•	Nothing happens unless you drive it. 
•	The best leaders value their people as people, not a commodity. 
•	Always be curious, always challenge.
•	Disruption and innovation are two sides of the same coin.

Please feel free to reach out via message or at Daniel.Sheridan@icloud.com.

My day-to-day job includes reviewing & modelling new site acquisitions, developing and presenting investment proposals to senior managers, collaborating with various teams to gain insights as to how we might improve existing sites, and analysing the performance of the existing network.

• Delivering more than 20 new site leases in New South Wales & Victoria, bringing a projected incremental ~$160 million cash flow per annum.
